accounts.name: transaction_bins
docs: The temporary account that holds the pubkeys of the bins being modified.

accounts.name: transaction_bins
docs: The temporary account holding the pubkeys of all bins for both old and new positions.

accounts.name: transaction_bins
docs: The temporary account that holds the pubkeys of the bins being read for fee calculations.

accounts.name: transaction_bins
docs: The temporary account that holds the pubkeys of the bins needed for the swap.
This account is created and closed in the same transaction.

accounts.name: referrer_fee_account
docs: The client is responsible for passing the correct token account for the input token.

accounts.name: authority
docs: The authority must sign for any fee update.

accounts.name: protocol_config
docs: The protocol config, to verify the signer is the true master authority.

errors.name: InvalidFeeRates
errors.msg: The provided fee rates are invalid.

errors.name: InvalidParameters
errors.msg: The provided fee and bin_step parameters are not on the whitelist.

errors.name: InvalidMintOrder
errors.msg: The mint addresses are not in the correct canonical order. Token A must be less than Token B.

errors.name: InvalidMint
errors.msg: The provided mint does not match the pool's mint.

errors.name: InvalidBinRange
errors.msg: The lower bin ID must be less than the upper bin ID.

errors.name: ZeroLiquidity
errors.msg: Liquidity to deposit must be greater than zero.

errors.name: SlippageExceeded
errors.msg: The market price moved unfavorably, exceeding your slippage tolerance.

errors.name: Unauthorized
errors.msg: The signer is not the authorized owner of this position.

errors.name: InsufficientLiquidity
errors.msg: The amount of liquidity to remove exceeds the amount in the position.

errors.name: PositionNotEmpty
errors.msg: Cannot operate on a position that has no liquidity.

errors.name: ZeroAmount
errors.msg: Input amount for a swap must be greater than zero.

errors.name: InvalidVault
errors.msg: The provided vault account does not match the pool's vault.

errors.name: InvalidBinId
errors.msg: The provided bin IDs must be a multiple of the pool's bin_step.

errors.name: RangeTooWide
errors.msg: The specified bin range is wider than the allowed maximum.

errors.name: MathOverflow
errors.msg: Math operation overflowed or underflowed.

errors.name: InvalidBinStep
errors.msg: The provided bin step value is invalid (e.g., zero).

errors.name: InsufficientLiquidityForSwap
errors.msg: Not enough liquidity in the pool to complete the swap.

errors.name: InvalidBinCount
errors.msg: The number of bins provided does not match the position's range.

errors.name: InvalidBinAccount
errors.msg: A provided bin account does not have the expected address.

errors.name: InvalidPool
errors.msg: The provided position account does not belong to the specified pool.

errors.name: BinCacheMismatch
errors.msg: The list of provided bin accounts does not match the cached list in the TransactionBins account.

errors.name: UpdateNotNeeded
errors.msg: The last update was too recent. Please wait before triggering another update.

errors.name: InvalidFeePreference
errors.msg: The selected fee preference does not permit this action.

errors.name: FeeShareExceedsTotal
errors.msg: The sum of protocol and referrer fee shares cannot exceed 100%.

errors.name: ReferrerIsTrader
errors.msg: The trader cannot be the referrer.

types.name: AmmPool
docs: State for a permissionless, constant-product AMM pool.
Follows the x * y = k model.

fields.name: bump
docs: The PDA bump.

fields.name: authority
docs: The authority that can update protocol fees or other admin-only parameters.
Can be a multi-sig or DAO.

fields.name: fee_growth_per_lp_token_a
docs: Total fees of token A accrued per LP token.

fields.name: fee_growth_per_lp_token_b
docs: Total fees of token B accrued per LP token.

fields.name: price_a_cumulative
docs: The cumulative price of token A in terms of token B.

fields.name: price_b_cumulative
docs: The cumulative price of token B in terms of token A.

fields.name: last_update_timestamp
docs: The timestamp of the last update to the reserves and oracle.

fields.name: price_a_cumulative_last_fee_update
docs: Snapshot of the cumulative price at the last fee update, used for volatility calculation.

types.name: AmmPosition
docs: Represents a user's liquidity position in a specific AMM pool.

fields.name: pool
docs: The AMM pool this position belongs to.

fields.name: owner
docs: The owner of this position.

fields.name: lp_token_amount
docs: The number of LP tokens this position represents.

fields.name: fee_growth_snapshot_a
docs: Snapshot of the pool's fee growth per LP token for token A.

fields.name: fee_growth_snapshot_b
docs: Snapshot of the pool's fee growth per LP token for token B.

fields.name: fee_preference
docs: The user's chosen strategy for handling accrued fees.

types.name: DlmmParameter
docs: A struct to hold a single valid (bin_step, fee_rate) pair.
Using a struct makes the code cleaner and more extensible.

types.name: DlmmParameters
docs: A singleton account that holds the whitelisted parameters for creating DLMM pools.

fields.name: authority
docs: The authority that can update these parameters.

fields.name: official_parameters
docs: Whitelisted parameters for "Official" pools created by the protocol authority.

fields.name: community_parameters
docs: Whitelisted parameters for "Community" pools created by anyone.

types.name: DlmmPool
docs: State for a Discretized Liquidity Market Maker (DLMM) pool.

fields.name: bump
docs: The PDA bump.

fields.name: authority
docs: The protocol authority that created this pool. For community pools, this is the creator.

fields.name: pool_type
docs: Distinguishes the type of the pool (Official or Community).

fields.name: volatility_accumulator
docs: Accumulator for market volatility, based on bins crossed during swaps.

fields.name: last_fee_update_timestamp
docs: The timestamp of the last dynamic fee update.

types.name: FeePreference
docs: The user's choice for how their LP fees should be handled.

types.name: PoolType
docs: Distinguishes between official and community-created pools.

types.name: ProtocolConfig
docs: A singleton account that holds the protocol-wide configuration,
including the master authority key.

fields.name: authority
docs: The master authority that can perform admin actions, like creating
official pools or updating protocol-level parameters.
